ğŸ“‚ File & Directory Management
ls â†’ List files and directories
ls -a â†’ List all (including hidden)
ls *.txt â†’ Files ending in .txt
ls ??.txt â†’ Files with exactly 2 chars before .txt
ls file[0-9].txt â†’ Files file0.txt â€¦ file9.txt
ls file[A-Z][a-z][0-9].txt â†’ Pattern match
cd â†’ Change directory
. â†’ Current directory
.. â†’ Parent directory
Absolute path â†’ Full path from /
Relative path â†’ Path from current location
touch file.txt â†’ Create empty file/update timestamp
